org.netbeans.swing.tabcontrol.plaf

Class BusyTabsSupport

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.netbeans.swing.tabcontrol.plaf.BusyTabsSupport
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BusyTabsSupport.DefaultBusyTabsSupport

    public abstract class BusyTabsSupport
extends Object
    Support class to implement animation in tab headers to indicate some sort of 'busy' state.
    install(Tabbed, TabDataModel)) and if any tab is marked as 'busy' (TopComponent.makeBusy(boolean)) it forces repeated repaints of that tab to allow animation effects. The UI of the tab container then can use an icon this class provides (getBusyIcon(boolean))to indicate the busy state. The default implementation of this class ensures that the icon is properly animated in each repaint.
    See Also:
    TopComponent.makeBusy(boolean)

        public abstract Icon getBusyIcon(boolean isTabSelected)

        Parameters:
